[{"id":"VR792787","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two systems of three point charges, labeled System A and System B. The three point charges have charges positive uppercase Q, negative 2 uppercase Q, and positive uppercase Q. In System A, the three point charges are arranged in a line, with the negative 2 uppercase Q charge in the center, and the two positive uppercase Q charges a distance s to the left and right of the 2 uppercase Q charge. In system B, the three point charges are arranged in an equilateral triangle with side length s, with the negative 2 uppercase Q charge at the topmost point and the two positive uppercase Q charges at the bottom left and bottom right points.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR792787.g03.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two different systems, each having three point charges, are shown in the figure. Each system has a negative point charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative 2 uppercase Q\"><math alttext=\"negative 2 uppercase Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>Q</mi></mpadded></math></span></span> and two positive point charges, each with charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive uppercase Q\"><math alttext=\"positive uppercase Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mpadded></math></span></span>. In System <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span>, the point charges are arranged along a straight line with each positive point charge at a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"s\"><math alttext=\"s\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>s</mi></math></span></span> from the negative point charge. In System <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span>, the point charge arrangement forms an equilateral triangle of side length <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"s\"><math alttext=\"s\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>s</mi></math></span></span>. Which of the following correctly compares the electric potential energies <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"U sub A\"><math alttext=\"U sub A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>U</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"U sub B\"><math alttext=\"U sub B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>U</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub></math></span></span> of the two systems? Take the potential energy of each system to be zero when the point charges are infinitely far apart from one another.</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR792787_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"U sub A is greater than U sub B\"><math alttext=\"U sub A is greater than U sub B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>U</mi><mtext>A</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>U</mi><mtext>B</mtext></msub></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"U sub B is greater than U sub A\"><math alttext=\"U sub B is greater than U sub A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>U</mi><mtext>B</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>U</mi><mtext>A</mtext></msub></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"U sub A equals U sub B, which equals 0\"><math alttext=\"U sub A equals U sub B, which equals 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>U</mi><mtext>A</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>U</mi><mtext>B</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"U sub A equals U sub B, which is not equal to 0\"><math alttext=\"U sub A equals U sub B, which is not equal to 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>U</mi><mtext>A</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>U</mi><mtext>B</mtext></msub><mo>â‰ </mo><mn>0</mn></mstyle></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":1}]